    <note>Huang(2) Gongqi [13002] According to Huang(2) Tingjian's [7111] funerary inscription for Yu(4) [13001], his first three sons--Gonglin (not in dataset), Gongyu [13003] and Gongji (not in dataset) all received the jinshi. Gongyu is listed in Nanchang FZ, with Gongqi and Gongjie [13004] after. Chronological logic, etc. would make these men at least nephews of Yu(4) and I am using them as surrogates for the missing sons (if they are not sons who changed their mingzi at some point after Huang(2) Tingjian's draft). Nanchang FZ, 29.4b.</note>
